ean\n- Reward dropped to -0.1, confirming only User3 is compromised\n- User3 still has Unknown compromise status\n- The -1.1 reward last turn was likely due to timing, not dual compromise\n\n**Strategy:**\nUser3 has Unknown compromise. I need to **Restore User3** immediately and aggressively. The pattern shows the attacker quickly escalates to Privileged on User3 and pivots to Enterprise0. Since Remove has failed before, Restore is the most reliable option to clean User3 before escalation occurs.\n\n`take_action(Restore, User3)`"}, {'role': 'user', 'content': '[(Defender, None, No, 4), (Enterprise0, Scan, No, 4), (Enterprise1, None, No, 1), (Enterprise2, None, No, 1), (Op_Host0, None, No, 4), (Op_Host1, None, No, 4), (Op_Host2, None, No, 4), (Op_Server0, None, No, 2), (User0, None, No, 4), (User1, None, No, 4), (User2, None, No, 4), (User3, None, No, 2), (User4, None, No, 1)]\nLast action: Succeeded.\nReward: -1.0.'}, {'role': 'assistant', 'content': '**Current State Analysis:**\n- User3 restored successfully - clean\n- **Enterprise0 is being Scanned** - attacker already pivoted!\n- Reward -1.0 confirms attacker has presence on Enterprise0\n- The attacker moved from User3 to Enterprise0 before the restore completed\n\n**Strategy:**\nEnterprise0 is being scanned with likely compromise (-1.0 reward). I need to **Restore Enterprise0 immediately** to prevent the attacker from gaining privileged access and moving toward Enterprise2 and the critical Operational subnet. Every second counts to prevent deeper penetration.\n\n`take_action(Restore, Enterprise0)`'}, {'role': 'user', 'content': '[(Defender, None, No, 4), (Enterprise0, Exploit, Unknown, 4), (Enterprise1, None, No, 1), (Enterprise2, None, No, 1), (Op_Host0, None, No, 4), (Op_Host1, None, No, 4), (Op_Host2, None, No, 4), (Op_Server0, None, No, 2), (User0, None, No, 4), (User1, None, No, 4), (User2, None, No, 4), (User3, None, No, 2), (User4, None, No, 1)]\nLast action: Succeeded.\nReward: -2.0.'}, {'role': 'assista